<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 6:08AM CDT  by NWS Kansas City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Andrew
and southwestern DeKalb Counties through 645 AM CDT...
At 608 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Country Club Villa, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clarksdale, Cosby, Amity and Helena.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
